"{\"uid\": \"theguardian.com-world-article-2024-jul-13-france-contemplates-chaos-after-the-general-election-with-no-clear-winner-and-the-olympics-just-weeks-away\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"The new national assembly meets this week, but what will happen if the three almost equal political blocs cannot agree on a prime minister?\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 139, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The new national assembly\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 25}, {\"ngram\": \"the three almost equal political blocs\", \"from\": 67, \"to\": 105}, {\"ngram\": \"a prime minister\", \"from\": 122, \"to\": 138}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One week after a snap general election that nobody won, and two weeks before it welcomes the world for theOlympic Games, France is still without a new prime minister or government and in political chaos.\", \"from\": 141, \"to\": 344, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 262, \"end\": 268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6175251420187262, \"rank\": 0.6193643132970962, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a snap general election\", \"from\": 156, \"to\": 179}, {\"ngram\": \"nobody\", \"from\": 185, \"to\": 191}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 230, \"to\": 239}, {\"ngram\": \"theOlympic Games\", \"from\": 244, \"to\": 260}, {\"ngram\": \"a new prime minister\", \"from\": 286, \"to\": 306}, {\"ngram\": \"government\", \"from\": 310, \"to\": 320}, {\"ngram\": \"political chaos\", \"from\": 328, \"to\": 343}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the French celebrate Bastille Day, the national 14 July holiday, the squabbling and stalemate between the three groupings that took the most seats but failed to secure a parliamentary majority continued with warnings that it could be two months before a solution is found.\", \"from\": 346, \"to\": 621, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 353, \"end\": 359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.5572176356321596, \"rank\": 0.7860293055242354, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Bastille Day\", \"from\": 370, \"to\": 382}, {\"ngram\": \"the squabbling\", \"from\": 414, \"to\": 428}, {\"ngram\": \"the three groupings\", \"from\": 451, \"to\": 470}, {\"ngram\": \"the most seats\", \"from\": 481, \"to\": 495}, {\"ngram\": \"a parliamentary majority\", \"from\": 517, \"to\": 541}, {\"ngram\": \"warnings\", \"from\": 557, \"to\": 565}, {\"ngram\": \"a solution\", \"from\": 601, \"to\": 611}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Asked what happens next, even experienced analysts are floundering.\", \"from\": 623, \"to\": 690, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"even experienced analysts\", \"from\": 648, \"to\": 673}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unlike its neighbours in Europe, France has no history of government coalitions and struggles with the concept of political compromise.\", \"from\": 691, \"to\": 826, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 724, \"end\": 730, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6175251420187262, \"rank\": 0.6193643132970962, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its neighbours\", \"from\": 698, \"to\": 712}, {\"ngram\": \"Europe\", \"from\": 716, \"to\": 722}, {\"ngram\": \"no history\", \"from\": 735, \"to\": 745}, {\"ngram\": \"government coalitions\", \"from\": 749, \"to\": 770}, {\"ngram\": \"struggles\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 784}, {\"ngram\": \"the concept\", \"from\": 790, \"to\": 801}, {\"ngram\": \"political compromise\", \"from\": 805, \"to\": 825}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c9meric Br\\u00e9hier, director of the Observatory of Political Life at the Jean-Jaur\\u00e8s Foundation thinktank, told theObserver: \\\"This has never happened before in France.\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 990, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 983, \"end\": 989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6175251420187262, \"rank\": 0.6193643132970962, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u00c9meric Br\\u00e9hier\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 841}, {\"ngram\": \"director\", \"from\": 843, \"to\": 851}, {\"ngram\": \"the Observatory\", \"from\": 855, \"to\": 870}, {\"ngram\": \"Political Life\", \"from\": 874, \"to\": 888}, {\"ngram\": \"the Jean-Jaur\\u00e8s Foundation thinktank\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 928}, {\"ngram\": \"theObserver\", \"from\": 935, \"to\": 946}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Like the UK, we are used to having a winner and a loser in elections.\", \"from\": 991, \"to\": 1060, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1000, \"end\": 1002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9218677439772754, \"rank\": 0.08475422602931267, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a winner\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1034}, {\"ngram\": \"a loser\", \"from\": 1039, \"to\": 1046}, {\"ngram\": \"elections\", \"from\": 1050, \"to\": 1059}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today, the reality is that not everyone has lost - apart fromEmmanuel Macronwho lost his gamble - but nobody has won.\\\"\", \"from\": 1061, \"to\": 1179, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the reality\", \"from\": 1068, \"to\": 1079}, {\"ngram\": \"not everyone\", \"from\": 1088, \"to\": 1100}, {\"ngram\": \"fromEmmanuel\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1130}, {\"ngram\": \"Macronwho\", \"from\": 1131, \"to\": 1140}, {\"ngram\": \"his gamble\", \"from\": 1146, \"to\": 1156}, {\"ngram\": \"nobody\", \"from\": 1163, \"to\": 1169}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The legislative election called by Macron, who surprised his own government with the decision, was billed as a means to \\\"clarify\\\" the French political landscape after the far right won the European elections.\", \"from\": 1181, \"to\": 1389, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1216, \"end\": 1222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.549750796579548e-42, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 1315, \"end\": 1321, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.5572176356321596, \"rank\": 0.7860293055242354, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}, {\"begin\": 1370, \"end\": 1388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2019_European_Parliament_election\", \"score\": 0.999999998961357, \"rank\": 1.0207249570861435e-09, \"text\": \"European elections\", \"types\": [\"Q40231\", \"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2019_European_Parliament_election\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2019_European_Parliament_election\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The legislative election\", \"from\": 1181, \"to\": 1205}, {\"ngram\": \"his own government\", \"from\": 1238, \"to\": 1256}, {\"ngram\": \"the decision\", \"from\": 1262, \"to\": 1274}, {\"ngram\": \"a means\", \"from\": 1290, \"to\": 1297}, {\"ngram\": \"the far right\", \"from\": 1348, \"to\": 1361}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead,it has brought confusion, threats from members of the three almost equal blocs that emerged to bring down any new government that failed to meet their approval, and unions warning of protests and strikes.\", \"from\": 1390, \"to\": 1602, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"confusion\", \"from\": 1413, \"to\": 1422}, {\"ngram\": \"threats\", \"from\": 1424, \"to\": 1431}, {\"ngram\": \"members\", \"from\": 1437, \"to\": 1444}, {\"ngram\": \"the three almost equal blocs\", \"from\": 1448, \"to\": 1476}, {\"ngram\": \"any new government\", \"from\": 1504, \"to\": 1522}, {\"ngram\": \"their approval\", \"from\": 1543, \"to\": 1557}, {\"ngram\": \"unions\", \"from\": 1563, \"to\": 1569}, {\"ngram\": \"protests\", \"from\": 1581, \"to\": 1589}, {\"ngram\": \"strikes\", \"from\": 1594, \"to\": 1601}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Last Sunday, the leftwing alliancethe New Popular Front (NFP)won 182 seats, Macron's centrist Ensemble group 168 seats, the far-right National Rally (RN), 143 seats and the conservative R\\u00e9publicains (LR) 46 seats.\", \"from\": 1604, \"to\": 1817, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1646, \"end\": 1659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Popular_front\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.5518014526985115e-12, \"text\": \"Popular Front\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Popular_front\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Popular_front\"}, {\"begin\": 1680, \"end\": 1686, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.549750796579548e-42, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 1738, \"end\": 1752, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"National Rally\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\"}, {\"begin\": 1804, \"end\": 1806, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LR_parser\", \"score\": 0.92780796616313, \"rank\": 0.07142709728078298, \"text\": \"LR\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LR_parser\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LR_parser\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"182 seats\", \"from\": 1669, \"to\": 1678}, {\"ngram\": \"RN\", \"from\": 1754, \"to\": 1756}, {\"ngram\": \"143 seats\", \"from\": 1759, \"to\": 1768}, {\"ngram\": \"the conservative R\\u00e9publicains\", \"from\": 1773, \"to\": 1802}, {\"ngram\": \") 46 seats\", \"from\": 1806, \"to\": 1816}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other diverse candidates picked up the remaining 38 seats.\", \"from\": 1818, \"to\": 1876, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Other diverse candidates\", \"from\": 1818, \"to\": 1842}, {\"ngram\": \"the remaining 38 seats\", \"from\": 1853, \"to\": 1875}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Without a compromise, no bloc can hope to form a majority of 289 MPs out of the 577-seatnational assembly.\", \"from\": 1877, \"to\": 1983, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a compromise\", \"from\": 1885, \"to\": 1897}, {\"ngram\": \"no bloc\", \"from\": 1899, \"to\": 1906}, {\"ngram\": \"a majority\", \"from\": 1924, \"to\": 1934}, {\"ngram\": \"289 MPs\", \"from\": 1938, \"to\": 1945}, {\"ngram\": \"the 577-seatnational assembly\", \"from\": 1953, \"to\": 1982}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The problem is that there is no justification that can be argued for this or that group governing.\", \"from\": 1985, \"to\": 2084, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The problem\", \"from\": 1986, \"to\": 1997}, {\"ngram\": \"no justification\", \"from\": 2015, \"to\": 2031}, {\"ngram\": \"that group governing\", \"from\": 2063, \"to\": 2083}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The only majority that exists is a majority that rejected the far right electorally and politically,\\\" Br\\u00e9hier said.\", \"from\": 2085, \"to\": 2200, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The only majority\", \"from\": 2085, \"to\": 2102}, {\"ngram\": \"a majority\", \"from\": 2118, \"to\": 2128}, {\"ngram\": \"Br\\u00e9hier\", \"from\": 2187, \"to\": 2194}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The left, which won the most seats, has spent days arguing since the election and achieving nothing.\", \"from\": 2201, \"to\": 2302, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The left\", \"from\": 2202, \"to\": 2210}, {\"ngram\": \"the most seats\", \"from\": 2222, \"to\": 2236}, {\"ngram\": \"days\", \"from\": 2248, \"to\": 2252}, {\"ngram\": \"the election\", \"from\": 2267, \"to\": 2279}, {\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 2294, \"to\": 2301}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It needs to come up with a name for prime minister.\", \"from\": 2303, \"to\": 2354, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a name\", \"from\": 2328, \"to\": 2334}, {\"ngram\": \"prime minister\", \"from\": 2339, \"to\": 2353}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If it fails, the president will take things in hand and name one.\\\"\", \"from\": 2355, \"to\": 2421, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the president\", \"from\": 2368, \"to\": 2381}, {\"ngram\": \"things\", \"from\": 2392, \"to\": 2398}, {\"ngram\": \"hand\", \"from\": 2402, \"to\": 2406}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Traditionally, the president asks the leader of the party with a majority to form a government and names a prime minister.\", \"from\": 2423, \"to\": 2545, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the president\", \"from\": 2438, \"to\": 2451}, {\"ngram\": \"the leader\", \"from\": 2457, \"to\": 2467}, {\"ngram\": \"the party\", \"from\": 2471, \"to\": 2480}, {\"ngram\": \"a majority\", \"from\": 2486, \"to\": 2496}, {\"ngram\": \"a government\", \"from\": 2505, \"to\": 2517}, {\"ngram\": \"names\", \"from\": 2522, \"to\": 2527}, {\"ngram\": \"a prime minister\", \"from\": 2528, \"to\": 2544}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The radical-left France Unbowed (LFI), the group that won the most seats in theNew Popular Front bloc, has proposed four candidates for prime minister, including the party's hardline leaderJean-Luc M\\u00e9lenchon.\", \"from\": 2546, \"to\": 2754, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2629, \"end\": 2642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Popular_front\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.5518014526985115e-12, \"text\": \"Popular Front\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Popular_front\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Popular_front\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The radical-left France Unbowed (LFI\", \"from\": 2546, \"to\": 2582}, {\"ngram\": \"the group\", \"from\": 2585, \"to\": 2594}, {\"ngram\": \"the most seats\", \"from\": 2604, \"to\": 2618}, {\"ngram\": \"theNew\", \"from\": 2622, \"to\": 2628}, {\"ngram\": \"four candidates\", \"from\": 2662, \"to\": 2677}, {\"ngram\": \"prime minister\", \"from\": 2682, \"to\": 2696}, {\"ngram\": \"the party's hardline leaderJean-Luc M\\u00e9lenchon\", \"from\": 2708, \"to\": 2753}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Socialist party (PS), which was due to meet on Saturday, is likely to propose its leader Olivier Faure, while the Communist party has suggested the relatively unknown Huguette Bello, president of the regional council on the French overseas territory R\\u00e9union.\", \"from\": 2755, \"to\": 3017, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2776, \"end\": 2778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialist_Party_of_Albania\", \"score\": 0.9999999991382538, \"rank\": 8.615639900687739e-10, \"text\": \"PS\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialist_Party_of_Albania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialist_Party_of_Albania\"}, {\"begin\": 2848, \"end\": 2861, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olivier_Faure\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olivier Faure\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olivier_Faure\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olivier_Faure\"}, {\"begin\": 2873, \"end\": 2888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communist_party\", \"score\": 0.8081815417766631, \"rank\": 0.20919511639885033, \"text\": \"Communist party\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communist_party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Communist_party\"}, {\"begin\": 2926, \"end\": 2940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huguette_Bello\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Huguette Bello\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huguette_Bello\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huguette_Bello\"}, {\"begin\": 2983, \"end\": 3008, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Overseas_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.532492466757797e-44, \"text\": \"French overseas territory\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Overseas_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Overseas_France\"}, {\"begin\": 3009, \"end\": 3016, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/R\\u00e9union\", \"score\": 0.9998511914873106, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"R\\u00e9union\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/R\\u00e9union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/R\\u00e9union\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Socialist party\", \"from\": 2755, \"to\": 2774}, {\"ngram\": \"Saturday\", \"from\": 2806, \"to\": 2814}, {\"ngram\": \"its leader\", \"from\": 2837, \"to\": 2847}, {\"ngram\": \"president\", \"from\": 2942, \"to\": 2951}, {\"ngram\": \"the regional council\", \"from\": 2955, \"to\": 2975}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Others have suggested finding someone above party politics.\", \"from\": 3018, \"to\": 3077, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Others\", \"from\": 3018, \"to\": 3024}, {\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 3048, \"to\": 3055}, {\"ngram\": \"party politics\", \"from\": 3062, \"to\": 3076}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WithFranceUnbowed and National Rally threatening to veto any government that includes the other, an alliance of moderates of the left, the Macron centre and the Gaullist centre right thrashing out a common programme appears the most promising solution.\", \"from\": 3079, \"to\": 3331, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3101, \"end\": 3115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"National Rally\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\"}, {\"begin\": 3218, \"end\": 3224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.549750796579548e-42, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 3240, \"end\": 3248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaullism\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.030386925101456e-18, \"text\": \"Gaullist\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaullism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaullism\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any government\", \"from\": 3136, \"to\": 3150}, {\"ngram\": \"an alliance\", \"from\": 3176, \"to\": 3187}, {\"ngram\": \"moderates\", \"from\": 3191, \"to\": 3200}, {\"ngram\": \"the left\", \"from\": 3204, \"to\": 3212}, {\"ngram\": \"a common programme\", \"from\": 3276, \"to\": 3294}, {\"ngram\": \"the most promising solution\", \"from\": 3303, \"to\": 3330}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An alternative, Br\\u00e9hier says, is a minority government through which each piece of legislation would require the forming of ad hoc alliances to pass.\", \"from\": 3332, \"to\": 3481, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"An alternative\", \"from\": 3332, \"to\": 3346}, {\"ngram\": \"Br\\u00e9hier\", \"from\": 3348, \"to\": 3355}, {\"ngram\": \"a minority government\", \"from\": 3365, \"to\": 3386}, {\"ngram\": \"each piece\", \"from\": 3401, \"to\": 3411}, {\"ngram\": \"legislation\", \"from\": 3415, \"to\": 3426}, {\"ngram\": \"the forming\", \"from\": 3441, \"to\": 3452}, {\"ngram\": \"ad hoc alliances\", \"from\": 3456, \"to\": 3472}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sylvain Maillard, from Macron's Renaissance, said his party would lodge a vote of no confidence if LFI was given power and suggested it would take time to find \\\"a greater coalition\\\".\", \"from\": 3483, \"to\": 3665, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3483, \"end\": 3490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sylvain_Cloutier\", \"score\": 0.9999999985839167, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sylvain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sylvain_Cloutier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sylvain_Cloutier\"}, {\"begin\": 3506, \"end\": 3512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.549750796579548e-42, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 3515, \"end\": 3526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renaissance\", \"score\": 0.9994082925383859, \"rank\": 0.0005589360370768664, \"text\": \"Renaissance\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renaissance\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renaissance\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his party\", \"from\": 3533, \"to\": 3542}, {\"ngram\": \"a vote\", \"from\": 3555, \"to\": 3561}, {\"ngram\": \"no confidence\", \"from\": 3565, \"to\": 3578}, {\"ngram\": \"LFI\", \"from\": 3582, \"to\": 3585}, {\"ngram\": \"power\", \"from\": 3596, \"to\": 3601}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 3630, \"to\": 3634}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"a greater coalition\", \"from\": 3643, \"to\": 3663}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said: \\\"We can live in a parallel world but mathematics shows [the left] have less than 200 MPs.\\\"\", \"from\": 3666, \"to\": 3765, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a parallel world\", \"from\": 3691, \"to\": 3707}, {\"ngram\": \"mathematics\", \"from\": 3712, \"to\": 3723}, {\"ngram\": \"the left\", \"from\": 3731, \"to\": 3739}, {\"ngram\": \"less than 200 MPs\", \"from\": 3746, \"to\": 3763}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Others see Macron, who until now has micromanaged the government, being forced to step back from domestic issues and concentrate on the presidential prerogative of defence and foreign policy, where the constitution allows him certain direct powers.\", \"from\": 3767, \"to\": 4015, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3778, \"end\": 3784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.549750796579548e-42, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Others\", \"from\": 3767, \"to\": 3773}, {\"ngram\": \"the government\", \"from\": 3817, \"to\": 3831}, {\"ngram\": \"domestic issues\", \"from\": 3864, \"to\": 3879}, {\"ngram\": \"the presidential prerogative\", \"from\": 3899, \"to\": 3927}, {\"ngram\": \"defence and foreign policy\", \"from\": 3931, \"to\": 3957}, {\"ngram\": \"the constitution\", \"from\": 3965, \"to\": 3981}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Last week, Macronpublished an open lettercalling for \\\"republican political forces\\\" to unite to build a \\\"solid [parliamentary] majority\\\".\", \"from\": 4017, \"to\": 4153, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4071, \"end\": 4081, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republicanism\", \"score\": 0.9998310977900257, \"rank\": 0.00016893074075587433, \"text\": \"republican\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republicanism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republicanism\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an open lettercalling\", \"from\": 4044, \"to\": 4065}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"solid [parliamentary] majority\", \"from\": 4118, \"to\": 4151}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Afterwards, conservative former prime minister Dominique de Villepin said that the new premier should come from the left.\", \"from\": 4155, \"to\": 4276, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4202, \"end\": 4223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominique_de_Villepin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dominique de Villepin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominique_de_Villepin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominique_de_Villepin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the new premier\", \"from\": 4234, \"to\": 4249}, {\"ngram\": \"the left\", \"from\": 4267, \"to\": 4275}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"One of the risks, if we continue with the current confusion, is that everyone will realise that no one has any political interest in leading this government.\", \"from\": 4277, \"to\": 4435, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the risks\", \"from\": 4285, \"to\": 4294}, {\"ngram\": \"the current confusion\", \"from\": 4316, \"to\": 4337}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 4347, \"to\": 4355}, {\"ngram\": \"no one\", \"from\": 4374, \"to\": 4380}, {\"ngram\": \"any political interest\", \"from\": 4385, \"to\": 4407}, {\"ngram\": \"this government\", \"from\": 4419, \"to\": 4434}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And that, in the end, the president will find himself faced with chaos.\", \"from\": 4436, \"to\": 4507, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 4449, \"to\": 4456}, {\"ngram\": \"the president\", \"from\": 4458, \"to\": 4471}, {\"ngram\": \"chaos\", \"from\": 4501, \"to\": 4506}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So he will face the question of whether resigning is the only way to resolve [the situation].\\\"\", \"from\": 4508, \"to\": 4602, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the question\", \"from\": 4524, \"to\": 4536}, {\"ngram\": \"the only way\", \"from\": 4561, \"to\": 4573}, {\"ngram\": \"the situation\", \"from\": 4586, \"to\": 4599}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first challenge will come on Thursday when the national assembly sits for the first time since the election to elect a president of the lower house - the equivalent of Britain's speaker - and the government officially resigns.\", \"from\": 4604, \"to\": 4834, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4776, \"end\": 4783, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9987141640875898, \"rank\": 0.0011464574648234582, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The first challenge\", \"from\": 4604, \"to\": 4623}, {\"ngram\": \"Thursday\", \"from\": 4637, \"to\": 4645}, {\"ngram\": \"the national assembly\", \"from\": 4651, \"to\": 4672}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 4682, \"to\": 4696}, {\"ngram\": \"the election\", \"from\": 4703, \"to\": 4715}, {\"ngram\": \"a president\", \"from\": 4725, \"to\": 4736}, {\"ngram\": \"the lower house\", \"from\": 4740, \"to\": 4755}, {\"ngram\": \"the equivalent\", \"from\": 4758, \"to\": 4772}, {\"ngram\": \"the government\", \"from\": 4800, \"to\": 4814}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since a 2008 constitutional revision inspired by the House of Commons' binary system, this has been followed by the designation of parliamentary groups including a majority party and a minority opposition and the distribution of committee and other posts.\", \"from\": 4835, \"to\": 5090, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a 2008 constitutional revision\", \"from\": 4841, \"to\": 4871}, {\"ngram\": \"the House\", \"from\": 4884, \"to\": 4893}, {\"ngram\": \"Commons' binary 